e beaming\neffect, we argue that the optical emission line luminosity may be a better\ntracer of ionizing luminosity for blazar-type AGNs and the black hole mass\nderived with the $R-L_{H_\\beta}$ relation are probably more accurate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Mar 2004 14:28:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
